name: auto-trader-clone
desc: An e-commerce style site modeled after auto-trader with NextJS, TypeScript, PostgresSQL.

name: date-night
desc: A full stack web app that funnels Yelp restaurant and event data. Uses Handlebars templating, Node, Sequelize/MySQL, auth0 and more!

name: dna-trans
desc: This website was built for a private, small business. The client expressed interest in increasing their search engine ranking to bring in more business online.

name: azuga-vehicle-locator
desc: A chrome extension developed for Azuga Fleet Management that allows users to view their Azuga GPS tracked vehicles within the dashboard of a ServiceTrade account.

name: burger-eater
desc: A different take on the todo list app built on a Node/SQL back-end. One thing that was fun/unique here was that I put together a simple ORM rather than use Sequelize.

name: reserve-a-car
desc: A mini Uber-like reservation system that allows a user to add a pickup and sources the closest vehicle/driver pairings to the user submitted location. MERN stack application.

name: chrono-cards
desc: A React built browser game where the user must avoid clicking the same card twice in a row.

name: fleetio-demo
desc: This feature gathers information on a Fleetio user's repair shop vendors, determines on average how long a shop has had a vehicle in service for a given repair and compares that against the standard book time repair data for the vehicles make and manufacturer. It even takes into account whether the shop was open or not, so as not to penalize a shop for not working in their off hours (it does this by fetching the shops hours from their Google My Business page). Built with Rails, React and Tailwind.
